B.afL=new A.iQ("Asian Carp","Hypophthalmichthys spp.","\ud83d\udc1f Fish","Large, fast-growing filter-feeding fish that outcompetes native species for food.","Can dominate biomass, reduce plankton populations, and harm native fisheries.","IL, IN, KY, MO, TN, AR, MS, LA, AL, IA, MN, WI, OH, MI, PA, NY")
B.afK=new A.iQ("Zebra Mussel","Dreissena polymorpha","\ud83d\udc1a Mollusk","Small striped mussel that forms dense colonies on hard surfaces like boats and pipes.","Clogs water intakes, damages boats, alters ecosystems by filtering plankton.","Found in 35+ states across the US and parts of Canada")
B.afR=new A.iQ("Northern Snakehead","Channa argus","\ud83d\udc1f Fish","Predatory fish with a snake-like head that can breathe air and survive on land for days.","Top predator that devastates native fish populations in ponds and slow rivers.","MD, VA, DC, PA, DE, NJ, NY, NC, AR, CA")
B.afQ=new A.iQ("Round Goby","Neogobius melanostomus","\ud83d\udc1f Fish","Small bottom-dwelling fish with a distinctive black spot on its dorsal fin.","Outcompetes native fish for food and habitat, eats eggs of native species.","Great Lakes region, spreading to inland waterways")
B.afO=new A.iQ("Spiny Water Flea","Bythotrephes longimanus","\ud83e\udd90 Crustacean","Small crustacean with a long tail spine that forms gelatinous masses on fishing lines.","Clogs fishing lines and downriggers, disrupts aquatic food webs.","Great Lakes and northern US states, parts of Canada")
B.afM=new A.iQ("Hydrilla","Hydrilla verticillata","\ud83c\udf3f Plant","Fast-growing aquatic plant that forms dense mats at the water surface.","Blocks waterways, crowds out native plants, degrades fish habitat.","Found in 30+ states from Florida to California")
B.afJ=new A.iQ("Sea Lamprey","Petromyzon marinus","\ud83d\udc1f Fish","Eel-like parasitic fish that attaches to host fish and feeds on their blood.","Has devastated Great Lakes lake trout and whitefish populations.","Great Lakes, Atlantic coast, Lake Champlain")
B.afI=new A.iQ("New Zealand Mudsnail","Potamopyrgus antipodarum","\ud83d\udc1a Mollusk","Tiny snail (4-6mm) that reproduces rapidly and reaches extreme densities.","Outcompetes native insects and snails that fish depend on for food.","Western US (MT, WY, ID, OR, WA, CA), Great Lakes, parts of Canada")
B.afP=new A.iQ("Rusty Crayfish","Orconectes rusticus","\ud83e\udd9e Crustacean","Aggressive crayfish with rusty spots on its shell that displaces native species.","Destroys aquatic vegetation beds, reduces native crayfish and fish populations.","Midwest, Great Lakes region, spreading eastward")
B.afN=new A.iQ("Eurasian Watermilfoil","Myriophyllum spicatum","\ud83c\udf3f Plant","Feathery aquatic plant that forms thick mats at the water surface.","Impedes boating, swimming, and fishing. Crowds out beneficial native plants.","Found in 45+ US states and most Canadian provinces")
